Under the following terms:

★ ATTRIBUTION — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the 
                license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so 
                in any reasonable manner, but not in any way that suggests 
                the licensor endorses you or your use.

★ NO ADDITIONAL RESTRICTIONS — You may not apply legal terms or technological 
                                measures that legally restrict others from 
                                doing anything the license permits.

==============================================================================
HOW TO PROVIDE ATTRIBUTION
==============================================================================

When using the Salamander Drumkit in your project, you must provide credit 
to the original author. Here are acceptable ways to do this:

1. In your software's "About" dialog or credits screen:
   "Drum samples: Salamander Drumkit by Alexander Holm (CC-BY 3.0)"

2. In your documentation or README:
   "This software includes drum samples from the Salamander Drumkit, 
    created by Alexander Holm and licensed under CC-BY 3.0.
    https://sfzinstruments.github.io/drums/salamander/"

3. In a CREDITS.txt file (recommended):
   See the accompanying CREDITS.txt file for full attribution information.

